{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #978: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $f\\in \\mathbb{Z}[x]$ be an irreducible polynomial of degree $k>2$ (and suppose that $k\\neq 2^l$ for any $l\\geq 1$).\n\nDoes the set of integers $n$ for which $f(n)$ is $(k-1)$-power-free have positive density?\n\nAre there infinitely many $n$ for which $f(n)$ is $(k-2)$-power-free?\n\nIn particular, does\\[n^4+2\\]represent infinitely many squarefree numbers? Current best: Hooley \\cite{Ho67} settled the first question, in fact providing a precise asymptotic for the number of such $n\\leq x$. Heath-Brown \\cite{He06} proved the answer to the second question is yes when $k\\geq 10$, and Browning \\cite{Br11} extended this to $k\\geq 9$ (in fact establishing an asymptotic formula for the number of such $n$). Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_021a646a7f72e0bf","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos978.erdos_978.variants.allow_fixed_divisors https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos978.erdos_978.variants.allow_fixed_divisors.","id":"vf_b4bdb0b5f48de557","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/978.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_021a646a7f72e0bf","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:978","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_b4bdb0b5f48de557","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:978","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed l